Former  Chairman of Inter Party Advisory Committee, IPAC, Enugu State, John Nwobodo, has emerged the governorship candidate of Accord Party (AP) in the state. Nwobodo, who was the sole aspirant of the governorship primary election, monitored by Independent National Electoral Commission (INEC), polled 140 votes through affirmation and was declared winner. The Chairman of Electoral Committee, Mrs. Chinasa Nwekeke, announcing Nwobodo as the winner, commended the delegates for conducting themselves in a peaceful manner. Nwekeke also commended members of INEC’s monitoring team for their patience throughout the process, stressing that with Nwobodo’s emergency, salvation has come to Enugu. In his acceptance speech, he commended the party and delegates for the confidence reposed on him as the governorship candidate. Nwobodo disclosed that his ambition to become the governor of Enugu was to right the wrongs, stressing that nothing has changed since 1999 till date.